  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Advanced HTML Forms?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Advanced HTML forms use enhanced attributes, validation techniques, and accessibility practices to improve user experience and data handling."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Form Attributes"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Attribute", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["action", "URL where form is submitted"],
          ["method", "HTTP method (GET/POST)"],
          ["autocomplete", "Enable/disable auto-fill"],
          ["novalidate", "Disable form validation"],
          ["target", "Where to display response"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Advanced Input Attributes"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Attribute", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["required", "Field must be filled"],
          ["pattern", "Regex validation"],
          ["placeholder", "Hint text"],
          ["readonly", "Non-editable field"],
          ["disabled", "Disabled field"],
          ["autocomplete", "Auto-fill support"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Example: Advanced Form"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<form action=\"/submit\" method=\"post\">\n  <input type=\"text\" name=\"name\" required placeholder=\"Name\">\n  <input type=\"email\" name=\"email\" required>\n  <input type=\"password\" minlength=\"6\">\n  <input type=\"text\" pattern=\"[0-9]{10}\" placeholder=\"Phone\">\n  <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n</form>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Custom Validation"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<input type=\"text\" required oninvalid=\"this.setCustomValidity('Enter valid name')\" oninput=\"this.setCustomValidity('')\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Fieldset and Legend"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<fieldset>\n  <legend>Personal Info</legend>\n  <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Name\">\n</fieldset>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Datalist (Auto Suggestions)"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<input list=\"browsers\">\n<datalist id=\"browsers\">\n  <option value=\"Chrome\">\n  <option value=\"Firefox\">\n</datalist>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Form Accessibility"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<label for=\"email\">Email:</label>\n<input id=\"email\" type=\"email\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use proper input types for validation**",
        "**Group related fields using fieldset**",
        "**Provide labels for accessibility**",
        "**Use pattern and required attributes wisely**",
        "**Validate on both client and server side**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Missing labels for inputs**",
        "**Overcomplicated validation rules**",
        "**Not handling server-side validation**",
        "**Using wrong input types**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Advanced HTML forms enhance usability, accessibility, and data accuracy. Proper implementation ensures better user experience and robust applications."
